@node ConfigBackup

This is both a backup, and a guide as to the meaning of each of the settings
of the config file.  The real config file does not have the comments,  so as
to speed up TCPFront's operation.

                       --------------------------------

File AmiTCP:db/TCPFront.config

/* Put the precise path and any parameters of your favourite email program  */
/* here to be executed ... leave blank if none wished.                      */
EMAILPROGRAM    =rx S:StoneREXX/REXXMailer.rexx

/* File in which TCPFront saves out a record of your connection times.      */
/* Useful for figuring out the phone bill in a shared flat. hehehe.         */
LOGFILE         =AmiTCP:PhoneLOG

/* Defines you connection type for TCPFront useage                          */
/* MAKE SURE YOUR DIALSCRIPT IS MODIFIED ALSO, IF YOU CHANGE THIS ANYTIME   */
Interface       =PPP

/* The following are shell (CLI) Commands to be executed at certain events.  */
/* Edit to suit your setup and personal taste.                               */
/* Leave empty for nothing to happen.                                        */
/* I personally use 'DSound' (which can be found on Aminet) which is a player*/
/* for IFF 8svx sound samples - but which spools off HD, wasting no precious */
/* RAM, which I'm a bit low on.  :(                                          */
/* These samples I use are included, as is the player, so just change the    */
/* paths to the sounds and you should be alright.                            */
/* Note : No quotes!                                                         */
Event_Caution   =Run >NIL: <NIL: C:DSound VOC:SCRComputer/Caution -2 -f -v64 -b45000 -w
Event_Disengage =Run >NIL: <NIL: C:DSound VOC:SCRComputer/Disengaging -2 -f -v64 -b45000 -w
Event_Offline   =Run >NIL: <NIL: C:DSound VOC:SCRComputer/Offline -2 -f -v64 -b45000 -w
Event_Dial      =Run >NIL: <NIL: C:DSound VOC:SCRComputer/Interference -2 -f -v64 -b45000 -w
@endnode

